#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:72
msgid ""
"As of Wesnoth 1.14, the antiquated SDL 1.2 library our engine used has been "
"replaced with the much-improved SDL 2.0. This addresses many longstanding "
"issues with OS and hardware compatibility. In particular, support for "
"fullscreen on multi-monitor configurations is greatly improved and various "
"mouse-related issues on Apple Retina devices are no more."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:74
msgid ""
"The user interface has also been further and refined and polished. The main "
"menu now features a crisper 4K resolution background and a brand-new main "
"theme from composer <a href=\"http://mattiaswestlund.net/\">Mattias "
"Westlund</a> (West). Larger and crisper fonts coupled with simplified dialog "
"borders and buttons enhance the game’s readability across a variety of "
"hardware and contexts, providing a more modern look. The add-ons manager, "
"multiplayer lobby and game set-up interfaces have been completely replaced "
"with fresh designs that we hope should address many long-standing "
"deficiencies in all of them. The preferences dialog has also been through a "
"substantial overhaul making it easier to navigate and use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:76
msgid ""
"A plethora of units such as the Heavy Infantryman and the Elvish Sylph have "
"received new animations and baseframes to bring them up to higher quality "
"standards and make the battlefield more lively and dynamic. There are new "
"generic portraits available for several units too, including the Walking "
"Corpse and Soulless. Finally, a <i>huge</i> number of new terrains have been "
"added to the game to enhance new and existing maps — especially those set "
"indoors and underground — and water and lava have been redone in a new, "
"fluid and fully-animated, aesthetically-pleasing style. Many village types "
"have also received time-of-day variations and will now immersively light up "
"when night falls."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:78
msgid ""
"Finally, the in-game sounds for many units and user interface elements have "
"been replaced."
msgstr ""

