#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:102
msgid ""
"Wesnoth’s multiplayer lobby has been redesigned from the ground up to "
"provide a simpler experience for new players getting the hang of the game. "
"New features include clickable links in the chat log, separate tabs for "
"private message exchanges, easier filtering of games and players, faster "
"game creation for those using a map author’s recommended settings, and a "
"more comprehensive display of faction attributes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:104
msgid ""
"In terms of content for games with other people, players will be glad to "
"know that the game’s roster has been expanded with no fewer than <b>nine</b> "
"community-contributed maps! Wesnoth now ships with a total of 55 carefully-"
"balanced maps with many different environments and team set-ups for players "
"to choose from."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:106
msgid ""
"The Khalifate multiplayer faction introduced in Wesnoth 1.12 has been "
"renamed the Dunefolk. This is part of an ongoing effort to expand their lore "
"and better ingrate them into the world of Irdya. Accompanying this are a "
"multitude of stats changes to various Dunefolk units aimed to better balance "
"the faction in multiplayer matchups."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:108
msgid ""
"It is now possible to forfeit a multiplayer game, signaling that you no "
"longer intend to keep playing without simply suddenly quitting."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><h4>
#: template.html:110
msgid "General"
msgstr "总体改进"

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><div><div><a>
#: template.html:113
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "<a href='images/start-6.png'>"
msgid "<a href=\"images/start-6.png\">"
msgstr "<a href='images/start-6.png'>"

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:116
msgid ""
"It is now possible to customize the colors of the movement/attack orbs "
"displayed alongside units on the map to make it easier for players with "
"different color perception to identify each unit’s status. An option "
"(disabled by default) is also provided to display a color orb on enemy units."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:118
msgid ""
"Switching to another application while Wesnoth is running now pauses the "
"music by default. If you'd prefer it to keep playing, there is an option for "
"that."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:120
msgid ""
"In order for players to more easily include details about their system when "
"reporting issues with the game, there is now a brand new version information "
"dialog accessible from the bottom-left corner of the main menu. Among the "
"information it provides are the operating system version, paths to the "
"various files Wesnoth uses, the version numbers of the code libraries the "
"game is built against, and a list of optional features enabled by the "
"packager."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:122
msgid ""
"Finally, for Windows players, the game’s configuration, saves, and add-ons "
"are now always stored in their Documents folder. This change was made to "
"avoid various issues inherent to the legacy approach of writing to the "
"system’s Program Files folder, which is neither recommended nor well-"
"supported on newer Windows versions. Note that while legacy option of "
"storing said files in the game’s installation path is gone, that behavior "
"may still be achieved through the use of certain command-line options for "
"those who prefer to install Wesnoth on an external drive."
msgstr ""

