#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:130
msgid ""
"This release series brings a major and long-overdue change to the way "
"Wesnoth content is licensed. While all content was previously required to "
"use the GNU General Public License version 2 or later for both code and "
"visual and sound assets, we now allow add-on creators to use <b>any</b> <a "
"href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/\">Creative Commons license</a> "
"for art, sounds, and music in their add-ons. Additionally, assets shipped "
"with the game may be licensed under the <a href=\"https://creativecommons."
"org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/\">CC BY-SA license</a>. In both cases, the GNU "
"General Public License continues to be supported. This change does not "
"retroactively affect any files previously published under the GNU GPL unless "
"the copyright holder chooses to relicense said resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:132
msgid ""
"With regards to more technically-oriented aspects, Wesnoth’s WML, Lua, and "
"Formula Language engines have seen a great number of improvements and "
"changes this release cycle. The internal Lua interpreter has been upgraded "
"to version 5.3.4, and much new functionality has been added to the <a href="
"\"https://wiki.wesnoth.org/LuaWML\">Lua API</a>. This includes the ability "
"to write <a href=\"https://wiki.wesnoth.org/MapGeneratorWML#The_lua_generator"
"\">map generators</a> using Lua, invoke certain stock dialogs used across "
"the game UI (menu popups, confirmation prompts, information pop-ups, the "
"<code>[message]</code> UI, and the story screen UI), and use named Lua "
"functions with the <code>lua_function=</code> attribute in <a href=\"https://"
"wiki.wesnoth.org/StandardLocationFilter\">Standard Location Filters</a>. The "
"Gamestate Inspector now also provides access to a built-in Lua console for "
"debugging and testing code directly within the game."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:134
msgid ""
"Inline formulas in the Wesnoth Formula Language have been enhanced with the "
"addition of many new built-in functions and syntax features. By extending "
"support for the <code>formula=</code> filter attribute to <a href=\"https://"
"wiki.wesnoth.org/StandardLocationFilter\">Standard Location Filters</a> and "
"<a href=\"https://wiki.wesnoth.org/StandardSideFilter\">Standard Side "
"Filters</a>, inline formulas can now be used to build more intricate logic "
"in WML. The new <code>~ADJUST_ALPHA()</code> and <code>~CHAN()</code> <a "
"href=\"https://wiki.wesnoth.org/ImagePathFunctionWML\">image path functions</"
"a> also include support for formulas to alter the rendering of images within "
"the game."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:136
msgid ""
"The WML preprocessor now supports optional parameters with default values in "
"macro definitions and substitutions by means of the new <a href=\"https://"
"wiki.wesnoth.org/PreprocessorRef#.23arg_and_.23endarg\"><code>#arg/#endarg</"
"code> directives</a>. This should enable authors to reduce code bloat in "
"situations where otherwise more than one definition of a macro would be "
"needed to cover varied use cases."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:138
msgid ""
"WML’s looping constructs are now more natural and flexible with the addition "
"of <a href=\"https://wiki.wesnoth.org/ConditionalActionsWML#.5Bfor.5D"
"\"><code>[for]</code> and <code>[foreach]</code></a> tags, making the "
"underlying syntax more lightweight compared to the old <code>{FOREACH}</"
"code> macro and hand-written alternatives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:140
msgid ""
"After several development cycles of adding new and/or experimental features "
"to the AI engine, a long overdue AI code cleanup effort was undertaken. This "
"includes a reorganization of the code of the current AI as well as the "
"removal of non-functional, outdated or deprecated code. As a result, the "
"format for configuring some AI parameters has been simplified and the AI "
"functionality has been augmented in many ways. To name just one example, the "
"functionality of the <a href=\"https://wiki.wesnoth.org/"
"DirectActionsWML#.5Bmodify_ai.5D\"><code>[modify_ai]</code></a> tag has been "
"extended significantly. Along the way, many bugs were fixed, such as "
"inconsistencies of dealing with hidden units, fog and shroud and a problem "
"with recruiting when the AI also had a recall list available."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:142
msgid ""
"As previously mentioned, <a href=\"https://wiki.wesnoth.org/ModificationWML"
"\">game modifications</a> can now be used in singleplayer campaigns as well "
"as multiplayer. Their syntax also sees the addition of a <code>[resource]</"
"code> tag to implement hidden modifications that can be explicitly requested "
"by add-ons instead of manually selected by players."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:144
msgid ""
"The map editor’s Open and Save As dialogs have been completely rewritten, "
"enabling easier access to the game’s files and installed add-ons, as well as "
"any other locations that can be saved for quick access as bookmarks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <html><body><div><div><p>
#: template.html:146
msgid ""
"Finally, content creators running the game on Windows might find the <i>"
"\"Battle for Wesnoth (with console)\"</i> shortcut useful. This includes the "
"new <code>--wconsole</code> command-line option, which enables a real-time "
"display of log messages in a standard Windows console instead of writing "
"them to a file. If keeping persistent logs as usual is preferred, we have "
"also improved the way those are stored on disk. Log files are now saved to "
"the <code>logs</code> folder in the player files path, and logs from up to "
"eight past sessions are stored in separate files with timestamps for "
"convenient reference. Finally, access to the current session’s log is "
"possible from the aforementioned version information dialog."
msgstr ""

